[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1075[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1076[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### Walkthrough
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1077[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1078[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 1: Enroll the patient and capture coordination-specific consent including caregiver setup and cross-organizational data-sharing posture.** Care coordination enrollment is more complex than the previous chapter 11 recipes because it involves not just the patient's consent but a structured caregiver setup with proxy-access scope, an inventory of the patient's clinicians, pharmacies, payers, and ancillary services, and a cross-organizational data-sharing posture that respects state-specific privacy regulations. Skip this step or treat it as boilerplate, and the entire deployment's regulatory and operational posture is compromised on day one.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1079[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1080[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1081[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ON enroll_patient(patient_id, target_population_segment,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1082[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                   legal_consent_form_signed,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1083[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                   state_of_residence,
