[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 3: Run the seam-detection rule engine on coordination-state changes.** Seam detection is the assistant's distinctive value. Each rule (medication-discrepancy detection, referral-non-scheduling detection, transition-of-care-incompleteness detection, test-result-acknowledgement-gap detection, conflicting-order detection, care-plan-item-aging detection, lapsed-coverage detection) is implemented as a deterministic check or, where probabilistic reasoning is required, a heuristic model with explicit confidence scoring. Rules have named clinical-leadership ownership, effective dates, and version histories. The rule engine evaluates rules on coordination-state changes and on a periodic sweep, surfacing detected gaps to the appropriate routing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ON coordination_state_change(patient_id, change_event):
