[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 4: Handle conversation entry with speaker-role identification, longitudinal context loading, and continuous emergency screening.** Every session begins with speaker-role identification (patient, caregiver, both), longitudinal coordination-context loading scoped to the speaker's role, and continuous emergency screening. Skip speaker-role discipline and the assistant accidentally surfaces patient-only categories to caregivers, breaching the patient's preference and (in some states) the law. Skip continuous emergency screening and the assistant misses an acute presentation in a routine coordination conversation, with potentially serious consequences.
