[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Performance benchmarks** (mid-sized payer or accountable-care-organization scale, 50,000 active engaged members, hybrid AI-plus-human-coordination program at six months post-launch). Numbers are illustrative reference points from production-grade deployments described in published industry case studies and are highly dependent on integration coverage, protocol-corpus quality, care-team workforce sizing, member engagement, and outcome-attribution methodology.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Metric | Target Range | Notes |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |--------|--------------|-------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Per-conversation latency (median, end-to-end) | 4-12 seconds | Multi-tool coordination flow with provenance retrieval and citation; latency is materially higher than single-tool conversational flows |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Per-conversation latency (95th percentile) | 12-30 seconds | Long-tail driven by cross-organizational data retrieval timeouts |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Engagement rate (% of enrolled members engaging in any given month) | 35-65% | Highly dependent on enrollment criteria, channel mix, and population characteristics |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Attrition rate (% disengaging within 90 days) | 15-35% | Calibrated to the population's coordination needs and the assistant's product fit |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Referral closure rate within protocol window | 60-80% | Improvement over baseline (typically 30-50% without coordination assistance) is the more meaningful comparison |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Transition-of-care completion rate within protocol window | 65-85% | Improvement over baseline (typically 40-60% without coordination assistance) is the more meaningful comparison |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Medication-reconciliation accuracy (vs. care-team-validated reconciliation) | 85-95% | Robust to most pharmacy-data-quality issues; benefits from strong pharmacy partnerships |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Seam-flag detection rate (true positives per active member per month) | 0.3-2.5 | Highly dependent on rule coverage and population characteristics |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Seam-flag false-positive rate | 5-25% | Calibrated by clinical-leadership review; rules with higher false-positive rates require additional verification before routing |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Citation-coverage rate (% of coordination-state assertions with valid provenance citations) | >98% | Launch-gate metric |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Scope-violation rate (% of conversations with detected scope violations) | <0.5% | Launch-gate metric; scope violations include diagnosis-attempted, treatment-recommendation-attempted, medication-titration-attempted, lab-interpretation-attempted |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Avoidable readmission rate (per 1,000 enrolled members per quarter, vs. matched comparison cohort) | 5-15% reduction | Multi-quarter to multi-year time-to-effect; attribution is observational, not causal |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Avoidable ED-utilization rate (per 1,000 enrolled members per quarter, vs. matched comparison cohort) | 3-12% reduction | Multi-quarter to multi-year time-to-effect; attribution is observational, not causal |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Patient-and-caregiver-reported coordination experience (composite score, 1-5 scale) | 4.0-4.6 | Leading indicator; reviewed weekly per cohort |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Caregiver-reported burden reduction (composite, vs. baseline) | 10-25% | Where caregiver presence is registered and consented |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Where it struggles:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Patients with poor integration coverage.** A patient whose primary care home, specialty providers, pharmacies, and ancillary services are mostly outside the institution's integration partners has limited assistant value. The integration-coverage band is a structural input.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Coordination across organizations with adversarial-interoperability postures.** Despite the Information Blocking rule, some organizations remain difficult to integrate with. The assistant operates with whatever partial picture is available, with explicit per-source coverage tracking.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Sensitive-record-category data flowing through partial channels.** A patient with substance-use treatment under 42 CFR Part 2 may have data that flows into one source but not another, producing a partial picture the assistant cannot supplement without violating the consent posture.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Patients with cognitive impairment without registered caregivers.** The assistant struggles to maintain the coordination relationship without a caregiver participant; the engagement model needs adaptation for these patients (the human care manager handles them).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **High-acuity coordination cases (multi-readmission, complex transitions, palliative-care planning).** The assistant escalates these to human care management; attempting to handle them in the assistant scope is unsafe.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Languages and dialects without validated translations.** Per-language asset development is multi-quarter clinical work.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Patients in situations the protocol corpus does not cover.** Unusual care transitions, rare-disease coordination, and complex pediatric coordination often need protocol-corpus extension.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Care-team workflow integration with poorly-designed tooling.** The assistant's value depends on the care team using its alerts; if the alert delivery is not in the team's workflow, the alerts get ignored.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Attribution challenges for outcome correlation.** Coordination effects are diffuse, multi-quarter, and confounded with other interventions (case management, value-based-care contracts, patient self-care). Outcome attribution is observational; rigorous causal claims require comparison-cohort design.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
